  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance to the Most Vulnerable Refugee and Migrant Populations in Peru Through Food Assistance and Cash Based Interventions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The crisis in Venezuela has resulted in the most severe and fastest growing population displacement in the modern history of the South American region. This project allows IOM the continuity of humanitarian operations currently being implemented in the northern region of Tumbes, bordering Ecuador, and the metropolitan city of Lima in Peru. The project focuses on interventions for food security, understood as availability and access to nutritious and healthy food; and the coverage of immediate basic needs of refugees and migrants from Venezuela through cash-based interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
